# Agent Discipline

Governance: `project-general.mdc`, repo root `AGENTS.md`. Multi-file workflow: `agent-multi-file.mdc`.

## Answer before you build

- Yes/no and advice → **direct answer in text first**, then code if needed
- Do not skip straight to implementation
- Do not refactor unrelated files while "helping"

## Next.js — docs before code

Training data is stale (Next.js `/docs/app/guides/ai-agents`). Before writing or changing `apps/app` behavior:

1. `nextjs-docs://llms-index` → `nextjs_docs` for the exact API
2. Do not guess App Router, cache, or Server Action behavior from memory
3. Runtime verification: `nextjs-mcp-quality.mdc` (stop hook runs `check:stability` when `apps/app` changes)

## Smallest layer (visual / UX)

| Order | Layer | Path |
|-------|-------|------|
| 1 | App wiring / previews | `apps/app/` — `frontend-app.mdc`; `theme-studio/`, `apps/storybook/` — `frontend-storybook.mdc` |
| 2 | Entity surfaces | `@repo/metadata-ui` — `frontend-metadata-ui.mdc` |
| 3 | Workspace compose | `packages/ui/.../compose/workspace/` — **ask the human first** |

A layout or polish request is not permission to refactor shared compose, surfaces, typography, or defaults.

## Do not repeat (learned the hard way)

- Rewriting `workspace-memory-lane.tsx` for a polish pass
- Flattening `workspace-shell.surfaces.ts` for Storybook contrast
- Changing `sidebarVariant` defaults to match an experiment
- `git restore` / `git checkout --` / `git clean` on untracked WIP unless explicitly asked

## When scope is wrong

Stop. Explain which layer fits. Ask: *"This requires changing `<file>` in workspace compose. Approve?"*
